      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oakdale%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town sits along the Connetquot River, where the historic Idle Hour estate once stood as a Gilded Age mansion.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6,
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://oakdaleislipneighborhood.org/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Dowling College once occupied the Idle Hour mansion, and its former campus remains a notable Oakdale landmark with waterfront views.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://oakdaleislipneighborhood.org/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Oakdale’s name may derive from a Nicoll descendant, according to local historian Charles P. in the mid‑19th century.",
